"n.熔合；聚变 【英】 n. 融合; 聚变(union of atomic nuclei) 【例】 the fusion of copper and zinc to produce brass n. (藉助热量对不同要素的)融合; 熔化; 联合; 核聚变 【记】可指: Jazz-rock 的fusion爵士摇滚乐 【参】fuse(n 保险丝; 导火索v 熔合) 【记】fuse 熔化，confusion 混乱就是 con + fusion 都融合到一块了 fusion (n.)  1550s, from Middle French fusion, from Latin fusionem (nominative fusio) ""an outpouring, effusion,"" noun of action from fusus, past participle of fundere ""pour, melt"" (see found (v.2)). In nuclear physics sense, first recorded 1947; in jazz sense, by 1972."
